    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-04-01T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-04-01T17:00:00-05:00" n="297"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d297">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.6363 ST 2/90: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-04-01T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 1, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:22 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. The Foreign Office informs me that the President is disposed to consider a
                    moderate and equitable settlement with the Standard Oil Company provided the
                    company recognizes the accusations against it.</p>
                <p>I made no comment since the decision rests with the company which would have to
                    acknowledge its guilt prior even to discussing a settlement.</p>
                <p>In making this suggestion the Government may be motivated by a desire to
                    temporize in anticipation of official representations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Norweb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
